{
    "id": "lightutil",
    "lang": "en-US",
    "name": "LightUtil",
    "description": "Set the mood of your world: turn an object into a light, tint the ambient sky/ground colors, and switch fog on with a chosen color and thickness.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-US/lightutil",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "lightutil",
        "light",
        "fog",
        "ambient",
        "atmosphere"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "CameraUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-US/camerautil"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "SceneUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-US/sceneutil"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "LightUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Lighting sets the **mood** of your world — bright and cheerful, dim and spooky, foggy and mysterious. `LightUtil` lets you add a light to an object, tint the overall ambient color of the scene, and control fog."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "note",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "The color methods here take a **color** value. Build one with [ColorUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-US/colorutil), for example `ColorUtil.FromRGBA(...)`."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Adding a light"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`AddLight` turns an object into a light source that brightens the area around it — like a lamp, the sun, or a torch."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "class Lamp",
                "{",
                "    void OnInit()",
                "    {",
                "        LightUtil.AddLight(this);",
                "    }",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Ambient color — the world's base light"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "**Ambient light** is the soft, all-over light that fills your scene even where no lamp reaches. It's split into three bands so you can give the light from above, the sides, and below different tints — for instance a warm sky and a cool ground."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "Tints the light coming from"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`SetSkyColor(color)`", "Above (the sky)."],
                ["`SetMedianColor(color)`", "The sides (the horizon)."],
                ["`SetGroundColor(color)`", "Below (the ground)."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Fog"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Fog hides distant objects in a haze. It's great for spooky levels, weather, or simply keeping the player focused on what's nearby."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`SetFog(true/false)`", "Turns fog on or off."],
                ["`SetFogColor(color)`", "The color of the haze (often matched to the sky)."],
                ["`SetFogDensity(amount)`", "How thick the fog is. Small numbers like `0.02` are subtle; larger numbers close in fast."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Switch on a light grey fog.",
                "LightUtil.SetFog(true);",
                "LightUtil.SetFogColor(ColorUtil.FromRGBA(0.6, 0.6, 0.6, 1.0));",
                "LightUtil.SetFogDensity(0.03);"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-015",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`void`", "`AddLight`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetSkyColor`", "`color color`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetMedianColor`", "`color color`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetGroundColor`", "`color color`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetFog`", "`bool enable`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetFogDensity`", "`float amount`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetFogColor`", "`color color`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-016",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "The fog methods affect the **whole scene**, so a single call changes the atmosphere everywhere. Match the fog color to your sky color for the most natural look."
        }
    ]
}
